Breakdown causes traffic jam near Edinburgh AirportMOTORISTS have been caught up in a traffic jam near Edinburgh Airport.The delays began when a car broke down on the M9 eastbound offslip to the A8 Glasgow Road, near Newbridge Roundabout.One lane was blocked for several minutes causing &quot;heavy delays&quot;, according to Traffic Scotland.The car has since been moved to the hard shoulder but the breakdown is &quot;still causing delays&quot; and drivers have been urged to slow down in the area.